Analysis
The file __PSScriptPolicyTest_yosxskxo.bsy.ps1 was created by powershell.exe in AppData\Local\Temp. Files with the naming pattern __PSScriptPolicyTest_*.ps1 are generated by PowerShell's execution policy enforcement mechanism when evaluating script policy. This occurs when PowerShell runs encoded commands or scripts and creates a temporary test file to check the current execution policy.
While this pattern is associated with legitimate PowerShell activity, it is also commonly observed during:

Execution of encoded PowerShell commands (-EncodedCommand flag)
Malware staging payloads in temp directories prior to execution
Post-exploitation frameworks writing scripts to disk

In this case, the activity was generated by an Atomic Red Team simulation (-EncodedCommand test) on WINLAB-01.

