Disposition
Verdict: True Positive — Simulated (Atomic Red Team)
The detection correctly identified PowerShell writing a script to a temp directory. In a real environment this would warrant immediate investigation of the PowerShell command line, parent process, and any subsequent execution from the temp path. In this lab context the activity was generated intentionally to validate the detection pipeline.

Recommendations

Enrich alert with command line data — Correlate Sysmon EID 11 with EID 1 (Process Create) to capture the full PowerShell command line at time of file creation.
Monitor for subsequent execution — Add detection for script execution from AppData\Local\Temp (Sysmon EID 1 with image path matching \Temp\*.ps1).
Tune false positive threshold — Raise Wazuh integration level threshold to 7+ to reduce noise from low-severity alerts.


